Based on the provided HTML code, I'll create a basic JavaScript code to add interactivity to the portfolio website. Here's the JavaScript code:

// Menu Toggle Functionality

const menuToggle = document.getElementById('menu-toggle');

const navLinks = document.getElementById('nav-links');

menuToggle.addEventListener('click', () => {

  navLinks.classList.toggle('active');

});

// Smooth Scrolling

const links = document.querySelectorAll('a[href^="#"]');

links.forEach((link) => {

  link.addEventListener('click', (e) => {

    e.preventDefault();

    const targetId = link.getAttribute('href');

    const targetElement = document.querySelector(targetId);

    targetElement.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth' });

  });
targetElement.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth' });

  });

});

// Form Submission Handling

const contactForm = document.getElementById('contact-form');

contactForm.addEventListener('submit', (e) => {

  e.preventDefault();

  const name = document.getElementById('name').value;

  const email = document.getElementById('email').value;

  const message = document.getElementById('message').value;

  console.log(`Name: ${name}, Email: ${email}, Message: ${message}`);
 logic here

});

This JavaScript code adds the following functionality:

1. Menu toggle functionality: Toggles the navigation links on smaller screens.

2. Smooth scrolling: Smoothly scrolls to the target section when a navigation link is clicked.

3. Form submission handling: Handles form submission and logs the form data to the console. You can add your own form submission logic here.

Make sure to correct the HTML code by replacing `mete` with `meta` and `initiai-scale` with `initial-scale`. Also, adjust the JavaScript code according to your needs.
